{"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol"],"title":"Inherits From"},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef"],"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TypeModuleProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","text":"ObjectProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypePluginProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject18TypePluginProtocolP","text":"TypePluginProtocol"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The model of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"text":" is a dynamically loaded module which","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements some number of types and interface implementations."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the module is loaded, it registers its types and interfaces"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.register_type"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.add_interface"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"As long as any instances of these types and interface implementations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are in use, the module is kept loaded. When the types and interfaces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are gone, the module may be unloaded. If the types and interfaces"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"become used again, the module will be reloaded. Note that the last"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference cannot be released from within the module code, since that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would lead to the caller’s code being unloaded before "},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"returns to it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keeping track of whether the module should be loaded or not is done by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using a use count - it starts at zero, and whenever it is greater than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"zero, the module is loaded. The use count is maintained internally by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type system, but also can be explicitly controlled by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.use"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject.TypeModule.unuse"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Typically, when loading a module for the first type, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_type_module_use()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be used to load it so that it can initialize its types. At some later","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"point, when the module no longer needs to be loaded except for the type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementations it contains, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_type_module_unuse()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"text":" does not actually provide any implementation of module","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"loading and unloading. To create a particular module type you must"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"derive from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"text":" and implement the load and unload functions","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModuleClass"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typemoduleprotocol"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TypeModuleProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypeModuleProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"TypeModuleProtocol","externalID":"s:10GLibObject18TypeModuleProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","symbolKind":"protocol","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"code":"GTypeModule","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a simple implementation of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"interface."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/interfaceInfos","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/name","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/parentInstance","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/typeInfos","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/type_module_ptr-lh1o","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/useCount"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/addInterface(instanceType:interfaceType:interfaceInfo:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/registerEnum(name:constStaticValues:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/registerFlags(name:constStaticValues:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/registerType(parentType:typeName:typeInfo:flags:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/set(name:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/unuse()","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/use()"]}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeModule":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typemodule","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypeModule"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TypeModule","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypeModule"},{"text":" provides a simple implementation of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTypePlugin"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"interface."}],"title":"TypeModule","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeModuleProtocol/use()":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"use","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typemoduleprotocol\/use()","title":"use()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the use count of a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModule","isActive":true},{"text":" by one. If the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use count was zero before, the plugin will be loaded.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If loading the plugin fails, the use count is reset to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"its prior value."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeModuleProtocol\/use()"},"doc://GLibObject/4GLib14PointerWrapperP":{"type":"unresolvable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","title"